{"lemma":"أَوانُ","slug":"أَوانُ","root":"#.#.ن","root_slug":"_-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/_-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1526","n1527"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"particular time, timeframe, occasion, time that has come or is due"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of إِنَاء (ʔināʔ, “vessel”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Middle Persian [script needed] (ʾwʾm), [script needed] (ʾʾwʾm /⁠āwām⁠/, “space of time; epoch; occasion”), from Old Persian *abigāmā f (“time”), from 𐎠𐎲𐎡𐎹 (abi-, “towards”) + Proto-Indo-European *gem- (“to press, to grasp”). Also borrowed in إِبَّان (ʔibbān).\n\nThe regular plural of إِنَاء (ʔināʔ, “vessel”) would have originally been *أَأْنِيَة (*ʔaʔniya), which became آنِيَة (ʔāniya, “vessels”) due to a regular sound shift affecting consecutive hamzahs. However, آنِيَة (ʔāniya) coincidentally has the form of a singular feminine active participle, so it appears to have been pluralized again to أَوَانٍ (ʔawānin, “vessels”) to reinforce its status as a plural."},"ipa":["/ʔa.waː.nin/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1526","headword_ar":"اَوَانٌ","root":"Awn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iwaAnN","text_ar":"اـِوَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb, K,) the latter mentioned by Ks on the authority of Aboo-Jámi', but the former is the usual mode of pronouncing it, (T,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awonN","text_ar":"اَوْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time; a season:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=winapN","text_ar":"ا=وِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, Msb, K;) but Sb says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=wnAtN","text_ar":"ا=وناتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M; [so in a copy of that work; app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=winaAtN","text_ar":"ا=وِنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=winapN","text_ar":"ا=وِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yinapN","text_ar":"ا=يِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=winapN","text_ar":"ا=وِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AA, T, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a A^awaAnu Albarodi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ اَوَانُ البَرْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season, of cold came"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaSonaEu *`lika AlA^amora","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَصْنَعُ ذٰلِكَ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=winapF","text_ar":"ا=وِنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yinapF","text_ar":"ا=يِنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=y^inapF","text_ar":"ا=يِنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does that thing sometimes, leaving it undone sometimes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu A=ynapF","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ ا=ينَةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda A=yinapK","text_ar":"بَعْدَ ا=يِنَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him times after times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=winapF","text_ar":"ا=وِنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time after time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) In the saying (of Aboo-Zubeyd, L),"},{"kind":"quote","text":"TalabuwA SuloHanaA walaAta A^awaAnK"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iwaAnK","text_ar":"اـِوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They sought our reconciliation"},{"kind":"text","text":"with them,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but it was not the time"},{"kind":"text","text":"that reconciliation should be sought], accord. to Abu-l- 'Abbás, the tenween of the last word is not a sign of the genitive case, but is, as in the instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*K","text_ar":"اـِذٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of the suppression of a proposition to which the word should be prefixed, as when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu A^awaAna qaAma zayodN","text_ar":"جِيْتُ اَوَانَ قَامَ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came at the time that Zeyd stood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAnay^i*K","text_ar":"اَوَانَيِذٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At that time"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season; then;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiynay^i*K","text_ar":"حِينَيِذٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Msb","K","L"]},{"entry_id":"n1527","headword_ar":"اـِوَانٌ","root":"Awn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAnN","text_ar":"اَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyawaAnN","text_ar":"اـِيَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}